Cephalon
(
Fig. 5D
) with suprantennal line bent downwards in middle; antennal lobes rounded. Eyes absent. Posterior margin of pereonite 1 convex, of pereonites 2, 3 straight, and of pereonites 4–7 progressively more concave (
Fig. 5A
). Pleonites 3–5 with small posterior points visible in dorsal view (
Fig. 5E
). Distal part of telson with concave sides and broadly rounded apex (
Fig. 5E
).
